'''Electromechanical coupling coefficient''' is a numerical measure of the conversion [[Energy conversion efficiency|efficiency]] between [[electrical]] and [[Acoustics|acoustic]] energy in [[piezoelectric]] materials.

Qualitatively the electromechanical coupling coefficient, k, can be determined as:

:<math> \mathcal{K}^{-2} = \frac{1}{\mbox{ energy converted per input energy}}  </math>

